Package: TaxaFlag
Title: Flag Anomalous Detections in Taxonomic Assignments
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Kevin", "Lafferty", , "klafferty@usgs.gov", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Identifies and flags anomalous detections in taxonomic
    assignment results from biological surveys. Detects laboratory and
    field contamination by comparing read proportions against control
    samples, flags handler-related artifacts near equipment setup or
    collection events, and provides LLM-based expert review of habitat
    fit, geographic plausibility, contaminant risk, and taxonomic scope.
    Operates on consensus data frames and appends categorical flag
    columns for user-driven filtering. Part of the TaxaID ecosystem.
